data.description: Wonderful home in Laurel Island Laurel Landing. As you enter the home the two guest rooms and guest bath are located off the foyer along with the laundry room and garage entrance. The foyer and laundry room have tiled flooring and all rooms have crown molding. The front guest bedroom has hardwood floors and a nice triple window bay for great natural light, the second guest room has a vaulted ceiling and hardwood floors. From the foyer you enter the incredible open floor plan, The living room has hardwood flooring trey ceiling. the dining room, Kitchen and flex/family room all have tiled floors.  The openness of the kitchen is so inviting for cooks of all kinds, granite counter tops with a breakfast bar, white cabinets, a lot of cabinet space with a separate counter area that would make a great coffee bar, stainless steel appliances built in microwave/hood and large walk in pantry. Flex family room has a built in fireplace and area above for you to install your entertainment items. Access to the screened in porch and fenced back yard is located in this room. The Owners retreat is located off the dining room area and has hardwood floors, a trey ceiling, and sitting area, Owners bath boats a double vanity tiled floors Separate shower and water closet and a whirlpool tub.  Need a large closet look no further than this owners retreat closet in the Owners bath with hard wood floors. The garage is finished with T1-11 wood siding makes hanging things much easier no need to find studs for most items. There is a water softener system and seller is leaving screen porch refrigerator freezer for you. Community amenities include use of pool, weight room and two play grounds within Laurel Landing exclusively for this subdivision only. Laurel Links public golf course is inside Laurel Island Community they have a wonderful food and beverage service available at Bogie's in Club house.  Conveniently located within minutes of I-95, Kings Bay Submarine Base, Shopping, Schools Restaurants and Medical/Hospital facilities Historical St Marys Waterfront and downtown Kingsland. Between 30 minutes to an hour from Jacksonville, Brunswick Florida and Georgia beaches.
